thread.title: Prep girls golf: Trojans 4th at district
thread.title_full: Prep girls golf: Trojans 4th at district

author: The Courier
title: Prep girls golf: Trojans 4th at district
text:
Comment: 0 
BOWLING GREEN — Findlay High junior Karina Bruce carded an 88 on Tuesday in leading the Trojans’ girls golf team to a fourth-place finish in the Division I district golf tournament at Bowling Green’s Stone Ridge Golf Club. Sophomore Emma Harris had a 94 and Jordan Whitman, a junior, and freshman Chloe Holliday had 97s as underclassmen combined for Findlay’s 376 total. Jackie Fontana, the lone senior on a young FHS roster, had a 102. Toledo St. Ursula earned the lone state-qualifying spot from the Northwest District tournament, carding a 321 team total to finish well ahead of Ashland and Perrysburg (367). Sylvania Northview’s Ashley Knight shot a 77 to advance to state with the best individual score from a non-qualifying team. 
DIVISION I GIRLS DISTRICT GOLF AT STONE RIDGE GOLF CLUB TEAM STANDINGS –1, Toledo St. Ursula 321. x-2, Ashland 367. 3, Perrysburg 367. 4, Findlay 376. 5, Sylvania Northvirew 377. 6, Wapakoneta 385. x-fifth-man scorecard playoff QUALIFYING TEAM: Toledo St. Ursula, 321. QUALIFYING INDIVIDUAL: Ashley Knight, Sylvania Northview, 77.
